[h1]Dated[/h1]
I don't know where to even begin. So here's a list of complaints:

[list]
[*]Character walks too slow. And the maps are huge. If you want to explore the maps for secrets and loot, be prepared for a slog;
[*]Teleport stations make you do a 1-minute walk to complete the teleportation. Yeah, that's right. Another slog. Like, you walk to the NPC that teleports you, select where you want to go, then it loads you on a walkway with little platform sections, then you get to your destination. It's genius;
[*]Lack of combo moves, compared to other games of the genre. Makes for combat consisting only of spamming the attack button;
[*]Dodge and block are the same button. So if you want to block, you better not have touched any movement keys in the last half-second, otherwise you'll dodge instead;
[*]Stiff controls that can be unresponsive at times. You click to jump, you don't, not unless you really, really pushed that button one second earlier than when you actually wanted to jump. It's frustrating;
[*]Long, drawn-out, boring busywork puzzles. They don't test your rationale, they test your patience;
[*]On Apocalyptic difficulty, why do we even have multiple life bars when most common enemies can just shrug off a whole life bar in one blow? Bosses make this even funnier, when one attack destroys 5 or more entire life bars from you. It's not about balance, it's about communicating to the player how much they're able to endure. As it is, you can never be sure if you're ready for a fight;
[*]The whole writing is dumb. Edgy protagonist being angry at all times, and everything and everyone being two-dimensional. I cringed at every cutscene, it's awful;
[*]Lots of glitches on the cutscenes and sound in general, being cut off randomly;
[*]Steam achievements are broken, requiring you to restart Steam every time before launching the game. That's because it needs to be the first game launched for it to sync your accomplishments. Did you know that game updates count as launching, at least in this aspect? So I had to replay two hours of the game from a previous save just to get the achievement I've earned. Also, there are no retroactive achievements here, nothing checks if you completed the requirements for one after you did, so you really need to keep restarting Steam and making multiple saves if you want them. Actually, not even all that works for some achievements. Good luck.
[/list]

